25|$|By late 1980s, the Soviet {{savings bank}} system had almost 80 {{thousand}} branches. As part <b>of</b> <b>Perestroika</b> reforms, in 1987 the savings bank outlets are reorganised into the Savings Bank of the USSR. Within the Savings {{bank of the}} USSR, separate savings banks were created in the Soviet Republics. Following {{the dissolution of the}} USSR, the former republican savings banks became state savings banks of the newly independent post-Soviet states.|$|E
